rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going pretty well, I will probably spend time with my friends and family members, do my normal routine and chores and take care of any business that I need to. I can see myself having a few good conversations with my best friend and setting up games to play with them too.
critical_positive: We had a lot in common, I could meet him on a lot of the topics and we laughed a lot and he wanted to know things I actually knew something about. So a lot of give and take was in the conversation, we had some personal talk, as well as talk about work, and what we enjoy as a hobby.
critical_negative: I would say it mostly went well and I can't think but a couple of times where I felt like I might be just filling up space in the conversation, but that wasn't too much of an issue but if I had to say something it would be that it lulled a couple of times and I had to pick it up.

rest_of_day_open: I think it is going to get better. It started off pretty rough and it would be hard to imagine it getting worse. Today felt like a load was taken off of my chest and it was nice to get to meet someone new and as friendly as she was.
critical_positive: We are both gamers in one way or another so that helped ease the tension between the two of us. Her grandmother is dying of Alzheimer's and mine just passed from it not too long ago which helped us create a connection as well. overall she was kind and easy to speak with.
critical_negative: Honestly the only thing that i thought was strange or did not work was at the beginning getting to know each other and breaking the ice. That really had nothing to do with me nor her it was just a bit awkward meeting someone over the internet. i havent had to do that before.
